text: Greenup County is a county located along the Ohio River in the northeastern part of the U.S. state of Kentucky. As of the 2020 census, the population was 35,962. Its county seat is Greenup. The county was formed on December 12, 1803 and named in honor of Christopher Greenup. == References == Category:1800s establishments in Kentucky Category:1803 establishments in the United States Category:Kentucky counties
title: Greenup County, Kentucky
